An employee of South African National Parks (SANParks) based in the Kruger National Park was trampled to death by an elephant and another sustained serious injuries.This occurred when a when a group of SANParks employees were attacked by a herd of elephants on Thursday in the late afternoon in the Mooiplaas Section of the Park near Mopani Camp.The circumstances for the attack are still being investigated, SANParks Acting Head of Communications, William Mabasa said in a statementThe Police and Medical professionals were called to the scene to assist the two employees who were attacked, but they could not save the one who had already lost her life when they arrived.The injured was rushed to a hospital in Tzaneen. On behalf of the SANParks Management and Staff; we would like to express our heartfelt condolences to the family, relatives and friends of the deceased; and to wish the other colleague who is currently in hospital a speedy recovery, said Mabasa.